CHOLERA - EAST AFRICA: REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Cholera - East Africa 971106225700
Cholera - East Africa (02) 971107232438
Date: Mon, 10 Nov 1997 13:33:53 -0800 (PST)
From: margaret russell <mlrussel@acs.ucalgary.ca>

Is the strain of cholera [bacillus that is causing the problem [in Kenya
and Tanzania known? While few international travellers benefit from
cholera vaccine, attenuated live oral cholera vaccine (eg., Mutachol -
Berna) may be useful for some who are working in the field, if the strains
"fit".
